[32m+[m[32m# 05 – Notifications and Analytics[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis stage extends the system beyond real-time ingestion and storage by introducing alerting, long-term data retention, and analytics capabilities.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhile DynamoDB serves as the operational data store for low-latency access to recent telemetry, additional services are integrated to support downstream use cases including alerting, historical analysis, and dashboarding.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Architecture Extension[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTo support these capabilities, the architecture is extended with additional AWS services:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m* Amazon SNS enables real-time notifications based on telemetry conditions[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m* Amazon S3 provides scalable and cost-effective long-term storage[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m* Amazon QuickSight enables visualisation and dashboarding[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTogether, these components transform the system from a data pipeline into a complete, production-ready analytics architecture.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 5.1 Amazon SNS (Alerts)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAmazon SNS is used to send notifications when telemetry values meet defined alert conditions.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn this project, SNS is used to detect abnormal sensor readings, such as elevated carbon monoxide levels, and trigger notifications without requiring manual monitoring.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Alert Flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```text[m
[32m+[m[32mTelemetry Payload → Lambda → Condition Check → Amazon SNS → Email / SMS[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Trigger Conditions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAlert conditions are evaluated within the Lambda function based on incoming telemetry values.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mTypical conditions include:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m* High carbon monoxide readings[m
[32m+[m[32m* Abnormal sensor readings[m
[32m+[m[32m* Missing or irregular telemetry datas[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample condition:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```Python[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mif co_raw >= CO_RAW_ALERT_THRESHOLD:[m
[32m+[m[32m    publish_alert()[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Publishing Alerts from Lambda[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Lambda function evaluates telemetry values and publishes an alert to Amazon SNS when a threshold condition is met.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample implementation:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```python[m
[32m+[m[32mco_raw = item["metrics"].get("co_raw")[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mif co_raw is not None and co_raw >= CO_RAW_ALERT_THRESHOLD:[m
[32m+[m[32m    sns.publish([m
[32m+[m[32m        TopicArn=SNS_TOPIC_ARN,[m
[32m+[m[32m        Subject="IndusStream Alert: High CO Reading",[m
[32m+[m[32m        Message=([m
[32m+[m[32m            f"High CO reading detected.\n\n"[m
[32m+[m[32m            f"Device: {item['device_id']}\n"[m
[32m+[m[32m            f"Timestamp: {item['timestamp']}\n"[m
[32m+[m[32m            f"CO Raw: {co_raw}"[m
[32m+[m[32m        )[m
[32m+[m[32m    )[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m[32mThis ensures that alerts are triggered automatically based on real telemetry conditions.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> The SNS topic ARN is configured using a Lambda environment variable.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Notifications Channels[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAmazon SNS supports multiple delivery mechanisms:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m* Email[m
[32m+[m[32m* SMS[m
[32m+[m[32m* Other subscribed endpoints[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor this project, email notifications will be used because they are simple and cost-effective.[m
[32m+[m
